author: Alex
title: SpaceX just launched a rocket and the footage is epic (4 photos and video)
text:
View as Slideshow 1 
SpaceX successfully launched its Dragon spacecraft at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center on Saturday, February 18. The unmanned craft, which is one of SpaceX’s Falcon 9 rockets, is en route to the International Space Station for a resupply mission. 2 
Ten minutes after liftoff, part of the Dragon broke away and flew back to earth before landing on the launch pad. 3 
The craft is hauling approximately 5,500 pounds of research equipment, cargo, and supplies. 4 
The equipment includes a crystal that is unable to grow to its full potential on earth due to gravity. In space, the crystal will grow to a size that allows scientists to examine how the molecules are arranged, providing new information on how they work in the body. 
There is also a 2,200 pound instrument onboard that measures the levels of ozone, aerosols, nitrogen dioxide and water vapor in the stratosphere.
